Tammy Petersen, News24 Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Durban &ndash; KwaZulu-Natal police on Monday appealed to the public for information about the murder of a mother and her two children.Police were called to the Mzungu area in Ndwedwe on Friday night, Lieutenant Colonel Thulani Zwane said.They found the bodies of Thandokwakhe Bhengu, 35, and her two children Lindelani, 16, and Lungisani, 8. The mother and teenager had been shot dead and Lungisani was hanging from a pole.The motive for the triple murder had not been established yet.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.